{
  "stem": "1061.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] and the interviewer is Chana Meier.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That summer in Lodz, when we met our uncle Alexander and established more or less a life, Lodz was not bombed out during the war as Warsaw was.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that there were all kinds of people returning, and all kinds of people trying to find their relatives or friends or whatever.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Anyhow, as I said, we lived with Uncle Alexander.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he left for Sweden, because his wife was taken from one of the camps to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he left us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Meanwhile, my sister, Krys married Miles Lerman.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my sister, Anna, the oldest one, went to Warsaw, to a school of-- the Polish school of diplomacy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we-- eventually, Miles decided that-- they sort of adopted me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Miles and Krys adopted me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they decided that I was going to stay with them until I get married, which, in fact, happened.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But Miles decided, and Krys that we would be leaving Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we went to Berlin, which at that time, set up a DP camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now we left for Berlin early on in 1946.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And as soon as we arrived, we discovered that there was a school for all the kids who came through the camps.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I was enrolled in the high school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "This time, everything was-- the courses were given in Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So I came out of the Polish high school, and now I now had something to show for, because I just, you know, I spent in the Polish high school about seven months now, or six, whatever.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Anyhow, Berlin was wonderful for me, because we were very pampered.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "All these kids that were coming in were really looked after, not only classes.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We were taken on excursions.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We were given extra chocolate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We had our own dining room, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Every effort was made to bring us out of that of-- of that experience, of the horror of the war that we came through.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we signed up for the United States, Miles, Krys, and I.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And by early of 1947, we left the Berlin camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I left the school with, with a report card of excellence and having made wonderful friends, whom I certainly have met later in America.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And we came to America, Miles, Krys, and I, on the boat, on February 11, 1947.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We were met at the boat by Miles's old aunt, who was 80 years old and her older husband.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they asked us if-- they took us to their apartment on the Lower East Side and showed us how to pull the string on the water tank for the toilet because-- and how to put the electricity on.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I thought that was very cute, because they left Poland about 80 years ago.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And as soon as we got settled, I went to high school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I'm still in high school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] First it was the Polish high school, then it was the Hebrew high school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Now it's the American high school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But this high school is for real.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And this was Thomas Jefferson High School in Brooklyn, where they established a special course for kids who had an education in another language, you see, who had qualified for high school, but by virtue of not knowing the language, weren't really qualified.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "So that we were enrolled in the regular courses plus a special course for the-- it was called Basic English, which was basically just orienting us to the educational system and so on.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And this-- I entered the school in 1947, graduated from high school in 1949, went to college, started Brooklyn College.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And I was recommended by a professor from Brooklyn College to become an instructor of Polish language at Indiana University, because they were looking for somebody.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And of course, having had my education interrupted all these times and, and having always hungered for more books and more knowledge, I said, no, I can't go.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Because I'm finally going to finish college.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "He said, no, don't worry.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] They'll accommodate you, and they would let you finish your own work-- your own-- get your own degree, which is exactly what happened.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Because within those three years that I spent in Indiana, they allowed me to teach three hours a day doing the regular course and six hours in the summer.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "So it worked out very well.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Of course, paid my tuition, and I was earning money.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "I was very happy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "I was self-support-- sustaining and self-supporting.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And I was by then engaged to Victor, whom I met in New York, before I went to Indiana.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And at that same time, Victor was in the army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "It was the Korean War.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
